news.title: Dozens weigh bids for Evergrande's Hong Kong headquarters
news.para: The deadline for submission of final bids for the tower, China Evergrande Centre, which is valued at between HK$8 billion and HK$9 billion ($1.02 billion to $1.15 billion), ends on Oct. 31.

news.title: Maharashtra government nod for town planning schemes in Uruli Devachi, Phursungi
news.para: The PMC and Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) had declared three TP schemes some four years ago for the two areas.

news.title: NAREDCO sets up finance committee to help builders in getting funds
news.para: The NFC will also support large-scale projects to access funds via financial institutions and educate members about the ways to enhance their credit ratings, NAREDCO said in its statement.

news.title: Dubai's luxury home market is booming as wealthy buyers flock to city
news.para: Demand for Dubai property is booming as the government’s handling of the pandemic and its liberal visa policies attract more foreign buyers. The luxury end of the emirate’s real-estate market is benefitting from an influx of wealthy investors such as Russians seeking to shield their assets, bankers fleeing strict Covid restrictions in Asia and rich Indians seeking second homes.

news.title: China to ease share financing rules for property-related firms but outlook bleak
news.para: The China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC) will allow certain companies with small property interests to raise money by selling A-shares, but the proceeds cannot be invested in the real estate business, China Securities Journal reported.

news.title: DLF's net profit increases by 26% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The board of directors of DLF approved enabling resolution for raising of funds through NCDs and/or other debt securities for an amount not exceeding Rs 1,500 crore.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' net profit dips 94% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's total consolidated income stood at Rs 7,244.78 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 7.48 per cent from Rs 6,740.57 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Motilal Oswal invests Rs 260 crore in three projects of Urbanrise-Alliance Group
news.para: The funds were raised towards three upcoming projects - 30 acres villa project on Kanakapura Road, Bengaluru, the seven acres high-rise apartment project in Whitefield, Bengaluru and the 17.5 acres of high-rise apartment project in Nizampet, Hyderabad.

news.title: SC seeks ED response on DHFL ex-CMD's plea for bail on medical grounds
news.para: A bench of Justices K M Joseph and Hrishikesh Roy asked the agency to file its reply within a week. "Counsel for the respondent seeks time to file a response. Put up for hearing on November 2," the bench said.

news.title: Bombay HC seeks special fire-safety panel to give its recommendation by year end
news.para: A bench of chief justice Dipankar Datta and justice M S Karnik had on August 22 granted Singh the liberty to place her suggestions before the committee and directed that she be given a personal hearing too by the panel.

news.title: Repair of 12 Bowbazar buildings possible: Mayor
news.para: The 12 buildings that have developed cracks after the latest subsidence in Bowbazar last Friday may not have to be demolished. Initial survey carried out by structural engineers indicate that repairs can be carried out.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body announces 'one time scheme' for property tax arrears
news.para: ​GHMC said the state has announced a waiver of 90% accumulated arrears' interest on property tax, provided taxpayers clears the entire amount.

news.title: Chennai corporation appeals to residents to pay property tax before Nov 15
news.para: Following the property tax general revision for the first half of the financial year 2022-23, the general revision for the second half has been done now and the payment portals was opened on October 1.

news.title: No development charge for projects developed on government land: Bombay HC
news.para: The bench dismissed 103 petitions filed mainly by builders and housing societies with development or redevelopment projects across the city on civic or state land.

news.title: Noida: Allahabad HC stay on demolition drive in Grand Omaxe till November 1
news.para: A group of 125 residents approached the Allahabad HC on September 30 and sought a stay on the demolition drive planned to be carried out in the society the same day. The court had then asked the Noida Authority to maintain status quo till the next date of hearing.
